  <prompt>
    <goal>Produce a structured inventory of Spaarke's AI touchpoints that live OUTSIDE the BFF process: S5 Foundry Agent Service overlap, S6 M365 Copilot / Declarative Agent surface, S7 Insights Engine MCP server. Output: projects/agent-framework-fit-assessment-r1/notes/02-non-bff-ai-touchpoints-inventory.md.</goal>
    <context>The fit assessment is incomplete without these surfaces. Foundry Agent Service is the canonical durable / HITL / A2A platform — Agent Framework's relationship to it must be clear before recommending adoption boundaries. M365 Copilot integration uses declarative agents + plugins — Agent Framework's role there is different from the BFF chat agent. The Insights Engine MCP is a separate deployable — the assessment must consider whether it should host Agent Framework agents.</context>
    <constraints>
      - READ-ONLY across all surfaces
      - For each surface: capture (a) current implementation status (production / in-flight / planned), (b) primary spec/design docs to cite, (c) which Microsoft.* abstractions are involved (or planned), (d) deployment model, (e) integration seam with BFF (if any), (f) HITL / durability requirements
      - Read project design docs and SPECs in each referenced project directory — these are the source of truth for in-flight work
      - S5 has no Spaarke code yet — inventory is from knowledge/foundry-agent-service/ + ADR-013 references + any project that planned to use Foundry
      - Where information is genuinely unknown, write "UNKNOWN (no current source)" — do not invent
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
