  <steps>
    <step>S5 Foundry Agent Service overlap: Read knowledge/foundry-agent-service/NOTES.md + SOURCE.md + docs/hosted-agents.md + docs/GAP-memory.md. Glob src/ for any Foundry-related code (FoundryAgentClient, AIProjectClient, Microsoft.Agents.AI.Foundry). Inventory: what's curated, what's planned, what (if anything) is in Spaarke code already</step>
    <step>S6 M365 Copilot / Declarative Agent surface: Read projects/ai-m365-copilot-integration/README.md + any SPEC.md/design.md/plan.md in that project. Inventory: Copilot integration approach (declarative agent + plugins? MCP?), how it surfaces BFF capabilities, whether Agent Framework agents host any of this surface</step>
    <step>S7 Insights Engine MCP server: Read projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r1/README.md + SPEC.md if present + the design docs under that project. Inventory: what the MCP server does, how it's deployed (separate from BFF?), what AI capabilities it exposes, whether it would host Agent Framework agents</step>
    <step>For each surface: capture the 6 fields from constraints (status / docs / abstractions / deployment / BFF seam / HITL+durability needs)</step>
    <step>Write notes/02-non-bff-ai-touchpoints-inventory.md with sections: S5 Foundry overlap | S6 M365 Copilot | S7 Insights Engine MCP | Cross-cutting observations (e.g., "two of three surfaces are external consumers; one is durable/HITL territory")</step>
